data.description: An Exceptional 2-Bedroom Rask Cottage with Stunning Lake Views! This Rask Cottage boasts a unique reverse floor plan, with the main entry leading to a gallery hallway, two bedrooms, and two and a half bathrooms. The master suite features a walk-in closet and an incredible lake view, while the second bedroom offers an en-suite bath and closet. The second level boasts 10' ceilings, with a large, open-plan kitchen, living, and dining area that opens onto a spacious terrace. Enjoy an unparalleled view of the lake and sunset from the walkout balcony. With a bathroom and laundry room also on the second level, this home is perfect for entertaining. This Green Building Certified home is part of the largest Geothermal community in the United States, featuring an energy-efficient and tankless water heater, thermostat, Geothermal HVAC and insulation. The private driveway includes an Electric Vehicle Port, and daily weekday trash pick up. Additionally, 19 beautifully landscaped parks are available for residents to enjoy. Trilith amenities include a resort-style pool, tennis/pickleball/basketball courts, and 15 miles of walking trails. The Piedmont Wellness Center and state-of-the-art dog park are also within easy reach. Conveniently located just 20 minutes from Hartsfield-Jackson Airport, there is plenty to do within steps of your door, including shopping, fine dining, and entertainment at the Trilith Live complex, which includes two live audience stages, an auditorium, movie cinema and movie studio. Take advantage of the robotic delivery of groceries by Nourish + Bloom Market located in the community. The Forest School, a K-12 micro school, is also located nearby.
